Afenifere, a Yoruba social-political organization has advocated for a Government of National Unity to tackle insecurity and other problems in the country. The socio-political organization maintained that the situation in the country is in a more decisive manner, stressing that in view of the seriousness of the situation and considering the fact that the present administration under President Muhammadu Buhari has shown that it is incapable and unwilling to tackle the identified problems necessitated the call for a Government of the National Unity. The meeting which was held at the country home of the Acting Leader, Chief Ayo Adebanjo reviewed the various challenges that Nigeria is facing particularly the choking insecurity that is threatening the country very seriously and agreed that the situation is now so precarious that no part of the country is safe at any time.  Attendance at the meeting includes some leaders and members of Afenifere from all the states in Yorubaland, including the former Deputy Governor of Lagos State, Senator Kofo Bucknor-Akerele, Chief Supo Sonibare as well as Chairmen and Members from the states.